article.headline: Swoopes scores 25 in loss
article.story:
SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Yolanda Griffith had 22 points and 11
rebounds, helping the Sacramento Monarchs to a 61-55 victory Friday
night over the Houston Comets.

Working the offensive boards and scoring from close range,
Griffith made 9 of 11 shots and all four free throws for the
Monarchs (4-7). Ahead 56-55, Ticha Penicheiro connected on a
3-point shot with 1:49 remaining.

Sheryl Swoopes produced much of the offense for Houston, scoring
25 points. Michelle Snow added 12 points and 10 rebounds. Felicia
Ragland had eight points.

The Comets (7-7) played without leading scorer Tina Thompson,
who missed her fourth straight game with a strained left calf.
Thompson scored 27 points earlier this season in a win over the
Monarchs.

Tangela Smith scored eight points for Sacramento. DeMya Walker
had seven points and eight rebounds. Kara Lawson also scored seven
points. Penicheiro added six points and six assists.

In a tight first half, Swoopes scored nine points to help
Houston to a 30-28 lead. Griffith kept the Monarchs close with 14
points.
